          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="content-guidelines" class="doc-h3">Content Guidelines<span class="h3-badge" style="background:rgba(37,99,235,0.1);color:var(--prism-violet);">Recommended</span></h3>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li>Use Large for prominent page-level progress; Small for dense lists or tables.</li>
                <li>Keep the label concise (2&#8211;4 words: "Upload progress", "Storage used").</li>
                <li>Show the % value alongside the bar so users can read the exact number.</li>
                <li>Transition to Success variant at 100% completion.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li>Use Large inside a compact list item.</li>
                <li>Write a full sentence as the label.</li>
                <li>Rely on bar width alone for precision &#8212; perception is inaccurate.</li>
                <li>Show 0% or a frozen bar while waiting &#8212; it implies the operation is stuck.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ========== STYLE ========== -->
        <div class="tab-content" id="tab-style" style="display:none;padding-top:32px;">
          <h2 id="style-overview" class="doc-section-title">Style</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Design tokens, colour mappings, and spacing tokens that define the Progress Bar's visual language.</p>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="variants" class="doc-section-title">Variants</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">126 variants across Variant (5) &times; State (2) &times; Fill Level (5) &times; Size (3) plus Indeterminate combos.</p>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Axis</th><th>Values</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><strong>Variant</strong></td><td><code>Default</code>, <code>Success</code>, <code>Warning</code>, <code>Error</code>, <code>Indeterminate</code></td><td>Semantic colour and mode. Use Indeterminate when duration is unknown.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Size</strong></td><td><code>Small</code>, <code>Medium</code>, <code>Large</code></td><td>Controls track height, typography scale, and vertical gap.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>State</strong></td><td><code>Default</code>, <code>Disabled</code></td><td>Default is the interactive/live state. Disabled applies greyed-out tokens.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Fill %</strong></td><td><code>0</code>, <code>25</code>, <code>50</code>, <code>75</code>, <code>100</code>, <code>N/A</code></td><td>Design-time fill percentage for static representations. N/A is Indeterminate only.</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

